HEADWORD: Euphonon
<hw>Eu"pho*non</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Euphony</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An instrument resembling
the organ in tone and the upright piano in form. It is characterized by
great strength and sweetness of tone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euphonous</ent>⟦br⟧
